HEADWORD: Tapa
<hw>Ta"pa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of cloth
prepared by the Polynesians from the inner bark of the paper mulberry;
-- sometimes called also <altname>kapa</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

